Currently we use prefixes like "c\_" for color, here is the full list:

- c - color
- d - distance
- t - t parameter, it's a "progress" of the curve
- a - angle taken from the pixel position to the closest point on the curve
  Base on those we know data type & what UI to display.

So user writes code like:

```
let fill = c_Color(s);
let progress = t_progress(s);
let dist = d_distance(s);
color = vec4f(fill.rgb, fill.a * progress * dist);
```

and the only additional thing we do it so add indicies. Because one program is composed of multiple effects/snippets and unique namign is nto guaranteed across multiple shader code snippets, with index suffic we make those unique.

```
let fill = c_Color_<program_index>(s);
let progress = t_progress_<program_index>(s);
let dist = d_distance_<program_index>(s);
color = vec4f(fill.rgb, fill.a * progress * dist);
```
